  "prompt": "Is spray paint waterproof?",
  "response": "Spray paint itself is not inherently waterproof, but many types are designed to be water-resistant once dry. The level of water resistance can vary based on the type of spray paint and the surface it is applied to. \n\nFor example, spray paints specifically formulated for outdoor use or for materials like metal or plastic are often more water-resistant than standard spray paints. Additionally, certain clear sealants can be applied over the paint to enhance its waterproof qualities.\n\nTo ensure the best results, always check the manufacturer's specifications and instructions for the particular spray paint you are using.",
